  <table border='0' width='100%' cellspacing='0' cellpadding='5'>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 bgcolor='black' class='header'>ITEM COMMENTS</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2><b><font color='#80000'>MORE TO IT THAN RAW NUMBERS</font>, By Vermillion</b><br><br>With regards to previous comment about having only a 100 point proc between the two of them as 1 handers, versus 175 as a single two handed. You're not looking really into it beyond just absolute values.  You see 175 vs 100, and saying that's just no contest. First, the delay on the 1 handed 100 damage proc weapon is less then the 2 handed. It may proc for less, but you sure as hell get a lot more chances to proc at it if you swing it more times.  You *nearly* swing it twice in the same delay time span as 1 swing with the 2 hander.  If you're lucky to proc both times, then you've done 200, clear.<P>
Second, working off the assumption DEX factors into whether or not something procs, the second 1 hander happens to boost your dex by a whopping 40 points as it's effect. Which would help the first proc quite often.Would be interesting though if you could proc the dex booster and then slap them back together and hack some more to try get more 175 procs with your newfound +40 DEX. Either way, yes, the proc is 100 on the 1 hander and yes, it is obviously less than 175, but you swing it more, and have more chances to proc, which in the long run, may or may not even out.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2><b><font color='#80000'>1H FORM IS THE WAY TO GO</font>, By Lyenae</b><br><br>In dual wield form, these two blades deal out 25% more damage. The 2h version should at least be 41/41.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2><b><font color='#80000'>I THINK YOU CAN USE BOTH 1HERS</font>, By Jaffa glimmercharm</b><br><br>I think you can use both 1H weapons at the same time.  If so, you'd get a major stat bonus for having both because you get the saves and procs from both simultaneously.  Also, dual wielding and double attacking builds up taunt faster than just double attacking, even if the weapon is more powerful than having 2 weapons.  Therefore, it lets a warrior do his job more effectively.  It's a difference of do I want to do damage (2H) or do I want to keep it on me (2 1Hers) so the other classes like rogues can do more damage?  Note that even with the ungodly ratio of the 2Her, a rogue with a ragebringer will do substantially more damage as long as they can backstab.  If you're grouped with a rogue, your best bet would be to go with the 2 1H weapons to keep it on you.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2><b><font color='#80000'>CONGRATS</font>, By Kavar</b><br><br>Duel wield means better taunt, sometimes hard to taunt off the casters, even with a great 2 Hander, especially if it is slow. Also from what I just read here, the self buff is right clickable, but only in the 2 weapons configuration? Not sure, just what I understood when I read it. Congrats to whomever has gotten this/these weapons.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2><b><font color='#80000'>I WOULD USE THIS  BOTH 2 OR 1 HANED</font>, By Hirosan</b><br><br>It really makes a diff on what your role is to be in the group, if your not the main tank then I would use it 2 handed for for the added damage that it can do, but if I was to be the main tank then I would go duel with it so I sould agro the mob faster on to my self. <br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
